nuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2562,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-vzpxn.4","author":"jemanuel","text":"CLOSED: WASI sandbox integration tested by 139 tests in wasi.rs. Tests cover: runtime invocation, component exports, policy enforcement, resource limiting via wasmtime ResourceLimiter. 409 total sandbox tests pass (270 egress + 139 WASI).","created_at":"2026-04-07T04:24:10Z"}]}
+{"id":"flywheel_connectors-w1098","title":"[REVIEW][MEDIUM] fcp-cbor: canonicalize_map scratch cap does not cap actual key-buffer growth","description":"crates/fcp-cbor/src/lib.rs:453-465, 497-500

Repro: build a large in-memory Value/map with oversized or deeply nested keys and call to_canonical_cbor() / CanonicalSerializer::serialize(). canonicalize_map_scratch_capacity() only limits Vec::with_capacity(); each into_writer(&key, &mut scratch) append can still grow scratch past MAX_CANONICAL_OBJECT_BYTES before any PayloadTooLarge check fires. Nested arrays/maps/interleaved key structures all hit the same path because key canonicalization serializes the fully expanded canonical key bytes into scratch.

